### 419.

<span id="page_215">p. 215</span>

Every shoot and every fruit is produced above the insertion \[in the
axil\] of its leaf which serves it as a mother, giving it water from the
rain and moisture from the dew which falls at night from above, and
often it protects them against the too great heat of the rays of the
sun.

